As the weather gets colder, there's nothing more festive than a pumpkin - and what's more wholesome than going to pick it yourself?

There are plenty of patches around South Yorkshire where you can do just that.

The top places to pick pumpkins include Pontefract's Farmer Copleys, Stirley Farm, Cannon Hall Farm, Williams Pumpkins at Castle Farm, Eastfield Farm Pumpkin Festival and Redwood Farm.

***Farmer Copleys in Pontefract offers a lot of different activities at its pumpkin festival(Image: Farmer Copleys)

There are farms growing pumpkins around the country, but there's one in Yorkshire that's particularly worth a visit.

Kett Country Cottages recently put together a ranking of the best pick-your-own pumpkin patches across the whole the UK, and Pontefract's Farmer Copleys came in at an impressive number two.

The Yorkshire farm offers an impressive pumpkin picking experience every year that's making a return for Halloween 2021.

Farmer Copleys has grown more than 130,000 pumpkins in preparation for the season - hailing from an impressive 27 different varieties.

The farm grows pumpkins in classic orange colours, as well as green and more, with type names such as the Baby Bear, Munchkin and Blue Crown Princes.
